Languages are now being valued as highly as STEM subjects (scientific, technology, technology and mathematics) in independent school programmes and elsewhere.
A 2014 UK Employment and Skills Commission survey revealed that 17% of the obstacles to filling vacancies were attributed to a lack of language skills, according to employers.
Thus language skills are becoming increasingly important to prepare young people for their future career.
