Regardless of the career that a person chooses, when he has learned a second language, he has a real benefit in the future with such skills for life.
Communicating directly with people from abroad automatically gives a multilingual person an advantage over competition.
According to a YouGov score of more than 4,000 British adults in 2013, 75 percent were unable to speak a foreign language well enough to have a conversation. French was the only language above 10%, with a total of 15 percent.
