Several languages, in particular those of emerging economies, will offer children a better chance of finding a meaningful job.
In Scotland schools themselves choose which languages they teach.
A number of schools will focus on the more classic modern languages, while other schools will teach which are most important for the United Kingdom when they look forward to 2020, such as Mandarin or Japan.
Whatever the interests of your child, there will always be different languages to choose in independent schools, with teachers specializing in this area.
Scottish independent schools set up to provide a learning environment that prepares children and gives them the skills needed to succeed, regardless of the future.
At the moment it cannot be denied that languages remain vital in a global business environment for the future of the country, so this must be reflected in education.
Modern languages should in fact be regarded as 'international communication skills'.
